## Conflict model
`notion-md` compares base, local, and remote body hashes. Non-overlapping edits can merge automatically; overlapping edits produce a Roughdraft conflict artifact.
## Demo identity
- Notion page: <mention-page url="https://www.notion.so/369f141b18dc80e4850cff344ad5b48e">@overeng/notion-md demo (automated)</mention-page>
- Local file: `packages/@overeng/notion-md/demo/showcase.nmd`
## Exhaustive feature showcase
This bottom section is intentionally broad. It keeps the basic demo readable above, then exercises the body and frontmatter-backed surfaces we expect the sync tool to preserve.
### Inline formatting
Plain text can mix **bold**, *italic*, ~~strikethrough~~, `inline code`, [links](https://developers.notion.com/), <span color="green">colored text</span>, and <span color="yellow_bg">highlighted text</span>.
Inline date mentions round-trip as enhanced Markdown: <mention-date start="2026-05-22" end="2026-05-23"/> and <mention-date start="2026-05-22" startTime="09:30" timeZone="Europe/Berlin"/>.
